main event: Numerous unidentified flying objects were sighted on the radar indicators of the 674th AC&W Squadron in Osceola, Wisconsin on July 29, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were observed traveling in a southeast direction at 50 to 60 knots and appearing in a loose formation, with some making turns and banks.
An interceptor pilot observed what appeared to be shooting stars or comets with tails when vectored toward the targets seen on the radar.
Weather data would have assisted in the analysis, but no new data was available for a more complete analysis.
Electronic sightings made and recorded by competent personnel.
Sightings were observed using ground electronic equipment as well as visually.
witnesses: officer controllers, airmen on duty at the 674th AC&W Squadron, two pilots from the 159th FTR Interceptor SQDN
